Inputs : 
  Quiz 1 mark
  Quiz 2 mark
  Quiz 3 mark
  Choice (Y/N)

Process : 
  User enters three quiz marks.
  Program calculates the average.
  Program checks if average is 50 or above.
  Program displays Pass or Fail.
  Program asks whether to continue.

Outputs :
  Average mark
  Pass or Fail
  Program Ended
  Pseudocode
  Start
  Set choice = "y"

While choice == "y"
    Input quiz1
    Input quiz2
    Input quiz3

    average = (quiz1 + quiz2 + quiz3) / 3

    If average >= 50
        Display Pass
    Else
        Display Fail

    Input choice
End While

Display Program Ended
End


Algorithm Structure
1\Sequence

Input marks
Calculate average
Display result

2\Selection

If average >= 50
    Pass
Else
    Fail

3\Iteration

While choice == "y"
